  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Brain-derived neurotrophic factor (BDNF), originally known to be a member of the nerve growth
      factor family, has aroused attention as a modulator in visceral hyperalgesia recently.
      Visceral hypersensitivity is recognized as a clinical hallmark in IBS patients. So in this
      study, the investigators will focus on the role of BDNF in colonic hyperalgesia in IBS
      patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
